<HR>
<H1>Complete Listing</H1>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="year501">Year 501: The Conquest Continues</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky</I></P>
<P>With chapters on Haiti, Latin America, the new global economic order, the
Third World at home, and much more, this is a powerful treatise on the
not-so-new world order. &quot;Year 501 is another awesome achievement by Noam
Chomsky. It is a devastating array of information about the U.S. role in the
world, placed in the long historical perspective of 500 years that followed the
voyages of Columbus. The result is a wonderful single-volume education in
history and world politics.&quot; &#151;Howard Zinn</P>
<P><I>0-89608-444-2 $16.00 paper . 0-89608-445-0 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="rethinkingcamelot">Rethinking Camelot: JFK, the Vietname War, and
U.S. Political Culture</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky</I></P>
<P>&quot;This book is a thorough analysis of John F. Kennedy's role in the U.S.
invasion of Vietnam and a probing reflection of the elite political culture that
allowed and encouraged the Cold War. Particularly important is his careful
delineation of the debate over whether Kennedy was about to withdraw from
Vietnam, a decision (some argue) aborted by his assassination in November 1963,
and Chomsky's analysis of the gulf between the general public and policy-making
elites. His larger argument is that Vietnam is just one more phase in the
European conquest that began 501 years ago. &#133; An interesting work not only
for the history it explores, but also as a study of how various individuals and
groups write and interpret history.&quot; &#151;Choice</P>
<P><I>0-89608-458-2 $14.00  paper. 0-89608-459-0 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="cultureofterrorism">The Culture of Terrorism</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky</I></P>
<P>This scathing critique of U.S. political culture is a brilliant analysis of
the Iran-contra scandal. And Chomsky offers a message of hope, reminding us
resistance is possible.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-334-9 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-335-7  $35.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="necessaryillusions">Necessary Illusions: Thought Control in
Democratic Societies</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky</I></P>
<P>Rips away the mask of propaganda that portrays the media as advocates of
free speech and democracy.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-366-7 $16.00 paper. 0-89608-367-5  $40.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="onpowerandideology">On Power and Ideology: The Managua Lectures</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky</I></P>
<P>
One of Chomsky's most accessible books, this short succinct series of lectures
lays out the parameters of his foreign policy analysis. The Nation called it, &quot;A
rigorous exposition [of] the logic of U.S. foreign policy.&quot;</P>
<P><I>0-89608-289-x $12.00 paper. 0-89608-290-3  $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="liberatingtheory">Liberating Theory</A></H3>
<P><I>Michael Albert, Leslie Cagan, Mel King, Lydia Sargent, and Holly Sklar</I></P>
<P>A collectively authored volume that provides a unique conceptual framework
for understanding contemporary U.S. society and history, and developing a
dynamic vision and strategy for social change.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-306-3 $12.00 paper 0-89608-307-1  $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="turningthetide">Turning the Tide: U.S. Intervention in Central
America and the Struggle for Peace</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky</I></P>
<P>Key to understanding U.S. foreign policy towards Central America in the
`80s, with valuable lessons for anti-intervention and solidarity work in the
90s. &quot;Better than anyone else now writing, Chomsky combines indignation
with insight, erudition with moral passion. That is a difficult achievement, and
an encouraging one.&quot; &#151;In These Times</P>
<P><I>0-89608-266-0 $12.00 paper 0-89608-267-9  $35.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="fatefultriangle">Fateful Triangle: The United States, Israel, and
the Palestinians</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky</I></P>
<P>&quot;This is a jeremiad in the prophetic tradition, an awesome work of
latter-day forensic scholarship by a radical critic of America and Israel.&quot;
&#151;Boston Globe</P>
<P><I>0-89608-187-7 $18.00 paper. 0-89608-188-5  $40.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="afterthecataclysm">After the Cataclysm: Postwar Indochina and the
Reconstruction of Imperial Ideology</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky and Edward S. Herman</I></P>
<P>Dissects the aftermath of the war in Southeast Asia, the refugee problem,
the Vietnam/Cambodia conflict, the Pol Pot regime, the question of human rights,
and the media's role.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-100-1 $16.00 paper. 0-89608-101-x  $40.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="washingtonconnection">The Washington Connection and Third World
Fascism</A></H3>
<P><I>Noam Chomsky and Edward S. Herman</I></P>
<P>Analyzes the forces that shape U.S. policy in Latin America, Asia, and
Africa, as well as the role of the media in misreporting these policies and
their motives.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-090-0 $16.00 paper. 0-89608-091-9  $40.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="sistersoftheyam">Sisters of the Yam: Black Women and
Self-Recovery</A></H3>
<P><I>bell hooks</I></P>
<P>With chapters on healing, addiction, stress, beauty, passion, critical
affirmation, love, reconciliation, and more, this book eloquently puts self-help
in a political framework. It will touch and motivate anyone who reads it. &quot;The
best example I've read of genuinely feminist books that do not privatize,
individualize and pathologize &quot;women's problems&quot; but rather put
problems into a larger political framework.&quot; &#151;Ms. Magazine</P>
<P><I>0-89608-456-6 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-457-4 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="blacklooks">Black Looks: Race and Representation</A></H3>
<P><I>bell hooks</I></P>
<P>In these twelve essays, bell hooks digs ever deeper into the personal and
political consequences of contemporary representations of race and ethnicity
within a white supremacist culture.  &quot;One of the 25 best books of 1992!&quot;
&#151;Village Voice Literary Supplement</P>
<P><I>0-89608-433-7 $14.00 paper 0-89608-434-5 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="breakingbread">Breaking Bread</A></H3>
<P><I>bell hooks and Cornel West</I></P>
<P>&quot;A series of dialogues between and interviews with two of the foremost
black intellectuals in America today, this volume is of enormous importance and
offers rewarding reading&#133;One of the 50 best books of 1992.&quot; &#151;Publishers
Weekly</P>
<P><I>0-89608-414-0 $14.00 paper 0-89608-415-9 $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="yearning">Yearning: Race, Gender and Cultural Politics</A></H3>
<P><I>bell hooks</I></P>
<P>Crosses disciplinary boundaries, boldly interrupting business as usual in
the major debates on postmodern theory, cultural criticism, and the politics of
race and gender. Winner of the Before Columbus Foundation's American Book Award.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-385-3 $15.00  paper 0-89608-386-1 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="talkingbalk">Talking Back: Thinking Feminist, Thinking Black</A></H3>
<P><I>bell hooks</I></P>
<P>An investigation of feminist theory written in an accessible style and
grounded in personal testimony, this volume includes chapters on feminist
scholarship, feminism and militarism, homophobia in black communities,
self-recovery, violence in intimate relationships, overcoming white supremacy,
and class and education.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-352-7 $13.00  paper. 0-89608-353-3  $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="feministtheory">Feminist Theory: From Margin to Center</A></H3>
<P><I>bell hooks</I></P>
<P>In this modern classic, bell hooks suggests that feminists must account for
the full diversity of female experience, including Black women's roles in
shaping feminist theory.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-221-0 $14.00 paper 0-89608-222-9  $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="aintiawoman">Ain't I A Woman: Black Women and Feminism</A></H3>
<P><I>bell hooks</I></P>
<P>A groundbreaking work of feminist history and theory analyzing the complex
relations between various forms of oppression. Ain't I a Woman examines the
impact of sexism on black women during slavery, the historic devaluation of
black womanhood, black male sexism, racism within the recent women's movement,
and black women's involvement with feminism.</P>
<P><I>
0-89608-129-x $12.00 paper. 0-89608-130-3  $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="educationforbuilding">Education for Building a People's Movement</A></H3>
<P><I>David Reed</I></P>
<P>
Provides a model for people to help themselves overcome their oppression,
understand society, and gain control over their lives. A tool for organizers and
teachers.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-121-4 $7.50 paper. 0-89608-122-2  $20.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="memoirofaracetraitor">Memoir of a Race Traitor</A></H3>
<P><I>Mab Segrest</I></P>
<P>Against the backdrop of the rampaging Far Right movement of the 1980s,
southern activist Mab Segrest probes the complex intersections of racism,
misogyny, homophobia, and capitalism. In these new essays and narratives that
are grounded in two decades of feminist, gay/lesbian, and anti-racist activism,
she moves from reporting to personal reflection to historical analysis in order
to focus on the primacy of racism in shaping U.S. history and its constant
complication by forces of gender and sexuality.  The book autobiographically
explores the history of  &quot;white&quot; consciousness in the United States,
the Civil Rights Movement, Southern culture,  neo-Nazis and the Klan, and
lesbian-feminism.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-474-4 $15.00 paper. 0-89608-475-2 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="stopthekillingtrain">Stop the Killing Train: Radical Visions for
Radical Change</A></H3>
<P><I>Michael Albert</I></P>
<P>This book does not simply say &quot;No&quot; to the &quot;killing train;&quot;
it says &quot;Yes&quot; to justice and liberation, offering detailed glimpses of
what society could be like and strategic advice for how to get there. &quot;Michael
Albert elevates common sense to an art form; he's funny, crotchety, irreverent,
and&#151;at all times&#151;on your side!&quot;&#151;Barbara Ehrenreich &quot;This
is a passionate, analytical, and visionary work. A must read for anyone willing
to accept the challenge of Albert's controversial and unrelenting intellect.&quot;
&#151;Juliet Schor</P>
<P><I>0-89608-470-1 $15.00 paper. 0-89608-471-x $35.00  cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="africanamericansatthecrossroads">African Americans at the
Crossroads: The Restructuring of Black Leadership and the 1992 Elections</A></H3>
<P><I>Clarence Lusane</I></P>
<P>Although liberalism still remains the dominant political ideology of the
black leadership elite, new political trends have emerged in the Black community
that challenge and critique the traditional liberalism of the Democratic party
as well as the neo-conservatism of the Republican party. Lusane uses the 1992
elections as a prism to explore Black community leadership and offers a
long-term vision of Black empowerment and resistance, inside and outside the
electoral arena.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-468-x $16.00 paper 0-89608-469-8 $40.00  cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="#chainofchange" HREF="#%23chainofchange">Chain of Change:
Struggles for Black Community Development</A></H3>
<P><I>By Mel King</I></P>
<P>One-time mayoral candidate, founder of the Rainbow coalition, and longtime
political activist, Mel King surveys black life in Boston, including the forces
of racism and liberation, and shows how the Black community has worked to
establish its identity, language, and organizations.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-105-2 $15.00 paper</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="#fromcivilrightstoblackliberation">From Civil Rights to Black
Liberation: Malcolm X and the Organization of Afro-American Unity</A></H3>
<P><I>By William W. Sales</I></P>
<P>From Civil Rights to Black Liberation is one of the few books that offers
historical research about the Organization of Afro-American Unity (OAAU), a
revolutionary organization founded by Malcolm X and rooted in traditions of
black nationalism, self-determination, and human rights.  The author establishes
the relevance of Malcolm's political legacy for the task of rebuilding the
movement for Black liberation almost thirty years after his assassination. Sales
intelligently argues why he considers Malcolm X more than an icon for
revolutionary African American youth; he asserts that he was a &quot;multi-faceted
thinker and organizer who is worthy of serious study by scholars, activists, and
anyone looking to understand our world today.&quot; &#151;Publishers Weekly</P>
<P><I>0-89608-480-9 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-481-7 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="#howcapitalismunderdevelopedblackamerica">How Capitalism
Underdeveloped Black America</A></H3>
<P><I>Manning Marable</I></P>
<P>&quot;A landmark study of the evolution of the Black community from slavery
to the present. [This book] is an important contribution to the understanding of
the U.S. race-class conflict. Its thoroughly researched, well-documented array
of statistics and historical data combined with powerful and well-reasoned
arguments make it required reading for those concerned with the problems of
achieving fundamental social change in America. &#133; Has in some repsects set
a standard of achievement for the current generation of Afro-American
scholar-activists.&quot; &#151;Race and Class</P>
<P><I>0-89608-165-6 $15.00 paper. 0-89608-166-4 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="#oncall">On Call: Political Essays</A></H3>
<P><I>June Jordan</I></P>
<P>&quot;On Call is one of the most insightful, powerful and internationalist
collections of political essays I have ever read&#133;should be read eagerly by
people around the world.&quot; &#151;Alice Walker</P>
<P><I>0-89608-269-5 $10.00 paper. 0-89608-268-7 $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="#pipedreamblues">Pipe Dream Blues: Racism and the War on Drugs</A></H3>
<P><I>Clarence Lusane</I></P>
<P>&quot;Lusane makes a cogent, convincing argument that the federal drug war
being waged in the nation's capital is parallel to that waged against other
communities nationwide and worldwide that seek justice, fairness, democracy, and
empowerment &#133; Lusane's solutions for addressing this problem reflect the
innovative and broad-minded perspective predominant in Pipe Dream Blues. &#133;An
important tool for understanding a problem that is popularly viewed in narrow,
stereotyped terms.&quot; &#151;San Francisco Bay Guardian</P>
<P><I>0-89608-410-8 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-411-6 $30.00 cloth</I></P></BODY></HTML>
