<html>

<head>
<title>Joining LOL</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFA" link="#FF0000" vlink="#FF0000"
alink="#FF0000" stylesrc="lolmainfr.htm">

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <h1 align="center"><font color="#FF0000">Joining Left On
        Line</font></h1>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p><font color="#0000FF">This page will allow users to
        join Left On Line on the fly by clicking and filling in
        some information. However, it is not quite ready for
        prime time use, as yet. </font></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p><font color="#0000FF">We should be prepared to take on
        new users by Sept 29, perhaps somewhat earlier. Please
        check back if you wish to join. </font></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p><font color="#0000FF">-- Thank You</font></p>
        <blockquote>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
        </blockquote>
    </blockquote>
    <h2>What Do You Get?</h2>
    <p><font size="3"><img src="images/grnhat.gif" align="bottom"
    width="32" height="32"></font> When you join Left On Line you
    get:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Membership in the community of Left On Line Users and
            Access to interaction with its members and use of its
            many tools, resources, guides, etc.</li>
        <li>Membership in the broader ShareWorld community and
            access to interaction with its members, forums,
            courses, use of its many unique facilities, etc.</li>
        <li>Internet guidance.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To see more details regarding specific LOL offerings
    consult the <a href="index.htm" target="_top">ZNet</a> or <a
    href="SWindex.htm" target="_top">ShareWorld </a>web sites,
    please, or examine the LOL site How To explanations.</p>
    <p>To join now click any of the Join Left On Line links on
    this page. You will then have to enter information in some
    forms, including credit card information, but once you are
    finished you will have full access on the spot.</p>
    <p align="center"><a
    href="http://lol.shareworld.com/chbin/main/logon?uid=guest&amp;pw=guest&amp;link=/chbin/mod/newuser"><font
    size="4"><strong>Join Left On Line&nbsp;</strong></font></a></p>
    <blockquote>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
    </blockquote>
    <h2>What Does It Cost?</h2>
    <p><img src="images/redhat.gif" align="bottom" width="32"
    height="32"> There is only one fee, with no variations. $8 a
    month for unlimited access. </p>
    <p>This includes forums, email, diverse information sources,
    access to many magazines and to the online magazine, <font
    color="#0000FF">Marble</font>, establishing and maintaining
    your own web site (with limits on size), extensive aid in
    navigating the Web, and unlimited use of various other
    facilities like activism on line, job banks, the book and
    magazine clubs, on line games, polls, and teleconferencing,
    etc. On Line courses are an extra fee, but are not available
    to anyone not belonging to LOL or to some other ShareWorld
    online community.</p>
    <p>To see more details regarding LOL offerings consult the <a
    href="index.htm" target="_top">ZNet</a> or <a
    href="SWindex.htm" target="_top">ShareWorld </a>web sites,
    please.</p>
    <p align="center"><a
    href="http://lol.shareworld.com/chbin/main/logon?uid=guest&amp;pw=guest&amp;link=/chbin/mod/newuser"><font
    size="4"><strong>Join Left On Line&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></font></a></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Why Join?</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>One reason to join is to get access to the many and
            varied resources of LOL and to the community of
            committed users of LOL and the other ShareWorld
            Systems.</li>
        <li>A second reason to join is to help support this
            ambitious project to bring the progressive and left
            community into telecommunications visibility. </li>
    </ul>
    <p><img src="images/yellhat.gif" align="bottom" width="32"
    height="32"> Eight dollars a month is not an insignificant
    cost to many users, we know. But developing and maintaining a
    comprehensive and cutting edge telecommunications community
    is a costly undertaking and we do not have access to large
    donor support, or to ad revenues (which we would not want, in
    any event--see <a href="lolmainfr.htm">About LOL</a>). So we
    must charge users directly and hope you will join in
    sufficient numbers to allow us to enlarge the left and
    progressive media presence as it deserves. </p>
    <p align="center"><a
    href="http://lol.shareworld.com/chbin/main/logon?uid=guest&amp;pw=guest&amp;link=/chbin/mod/newuser"><font
    size="4"><strong>Join Left On Line&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></font></a></p>
    <p align="center">&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>How Do You Join?</h2>
    <p><img src="images/bluehat.gif" align="bottom" width="32"
    height="32"> Joining is simple. </p>
    <p>Just click the button located directly below and then fill
    out the requisite form so we can charge your credit card each
    month, and you are a member. It happens online, on the spot.
    You can discontinue your membership at any time, of course,
    though there are no refunds for prior fees paid.</p>
    <p>If you do not have a credit card, you can join for 6
    months at a time, for a fee of $50, or for a year, for a fee
    of $100, by sending a check with the user id you would like
    to have on the system (usually one's name, adapted a bit to
    be unique) and a password (4 to 9 characters) to....</p>
    <p align="center"><a
    href="http://lol.shareworld.com/chbin/main/logon?uid=guest&amp;pw=guest&amp;link=/chbin/mod/newuser"><font
    size="4"><strong>Join Left On Line&nbsp;</strong></font></a></p>
</blockquote>
</body>
