<body bgcolor="#C7C712">
<h4><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld Online 
Communities</strong></em></font></font></h4>
<p><img src="images/hhome.gif" alt="[Page Banner Image]" align=bottom width=472 height=48> </p>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld's Mission</h2>
<p>Shareworld is dedicated to fostering the progressive use of telecommunications by providing 
tailor-made online systems to diverse organizations and by developing varied content and 
functionality for the community of all those systems taken together. To find out more about our 
systems, their options and functionality, and how our clients and users benefit, please choose 
<a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, here or above. There is extensive description and further links, but there are also numerous 
screen shots, and please be warned that these may take a little while to load...</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld's Company Profile</h2>
<p>ShareWorld has a variety of company components including a <a href="SWtech.htm">technical arm</a>, for developing and 
maintaining online systems, a <a href="swpromo.htm">promotion and solicitation arm</a>, for signing clients and users up to these 
various systems, and an <a href="swedit.htm">&quot;editorial&quot; arm</a>, for developing content to share on these systems. </p>
<p>ShareWorld also includes, however, all the <a href="swconsti.htm">constitutency organizations</a> who contract for systems 
and help to maintain them and provide contents for them.</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld's Clients</h2>
<p>ShareWorld contracts with client organizations to create for them and their constituencies online 
systems accessible by telnet and local call access from throughout the country. These online systems 
provide full internet connectivity, of course and interface seamlessly with the World Wide Web, but 
also provide a great deal of <a href="serv01.htm">additional functionality</a>, beyond typical web sites, rather like having an 
America On Line for your own organization.</p>
<p>Additionally, the sum total of all ShareWorld created systems constitutes a <a href="swconsti.htm">larger community of 
online projects</a>, each sharing many of its resources of the rest. </p>
<p>ShareWorld's first clients are The Nation Magazine sponsoring Nation on Line, the Wilderness 
Society sponsoring Wilderness On Line, and a consortium of organizations sponsoring Left on Line. 
A number of other potential clients are currently negotiating and additional ones are first being 
contacted.</p>
<p>For more about ShareWorld's offerings, please select <a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, either here or in the menu bar at the 
top of this page. You might also be interested in ShareWorld's Guide to the Internet, in the 
<a href="Wild/GUIDE.HTM">Wilderness Guide to the Internet</a>, in the <a href="http://www.thenation.com">Nations extensive web site</a>, or in the <a href="LOL/guide.html">Left on Line Guide to 
the Internet</a>.</p>
<p>A final, particularly nice thing about ShareWorld Systems is that you can join a ShareWorld System 
from online, even from a web browser, should you decide you wish to after reading about the 
various services and other offerings these systems have.</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
