<h1 align="center"><font color="#FF0000">Additional LOL Options</font></h1>

<hr>

<blockquote>
    <p>All <a href="http://www.shareworld.com">ShareWorld</a>
    online systems (and Left On Line is one) offer (or will soon
    offer) a host of different capabilities and options including
    but not limited to:</p>
    <blockquote>
        <ul>
            <li>A congenial, civil, supportive community of users</li>
            <li>Friendly, informed, tech support</li>
            <li>Diverse offerings from the many sponsoring
                organizations, such as The Nation, The Wilderness
                Society, etc.</li>
            <li>Full text search file libraries of diverse
                articles</li>
            <li>Extensive guidance with Web Browsing, regularly
                updated</li>
            <li>E-Mail far and wide, with formating, spell
                checking, and web links</li>
            <li>Political and educational Forums often with noted
                activists and scholars--serious substantive
                exchange, moderated, and without harassment,
                sexism, flaming, etc.</li>
            <li>Online university and high school courses from
                fantastic faculty</li>
            <li>Polls and agenda setting </li>
            <li>Book and Magazine Clubs with discussion groups,
                reduced rate purchasing, etc.</li>
            <li>Teleconferencing with audio capability...(coming)</li>
            <li>A Children's Center and Children&#146;s Internet
                help including the ability to limit web browsing
                access</li>
            <li>Sensible adult socializing, an on line buddy
                system, and internet help for adults</li>
            <li>A weekly international magazine, Marble</li>
            <li>A weekly user edited and written magazine from
                the ShareWorld community's members</li>
            <li>A poetry center for contributions from members of
                any ShareWorld System community</li>
            <li>Activism on Line by fax and email</li>
            <li>Job offerings on line where people can post and
                find listings</li>
            <li>Alternative Radio (coming) </li>
            <li>Issues and events announcements by system
                operators and users</li>
            <li>Games like chess and checkers online that people
                can play simultaneously or a move at a time like
                email</li>
            <li>Audio calls without long distance
                fees&#133;(coming)</li>
            <li>Offerings from the rest of the ShareWorld
                Community<br>
                And much more&#133;.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The easiest way to get a good feeling for the breadth
        of content and ease of use of the Left On Line system is
        to <a
        href="http://www.lol.shareworld.com/leftonl/lolentry.htm"
        target="_top">Visit LOL</a>. Even as a non member you can
        look around enough to get a reasonable feel for its
        offerings... But please, if you like what you see, join.
        There are no ads, no commercials, no way to fund this
        outside of support from our user community.</p>
        <table border="0" cellpadding="2" width="100%">
