<H1>Leasing the Ivory Tower</H1>   
<IMG SRC="lease2.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE">
<H2>The Corporate Takeover of Academia</H2>
<H3>By Lawrence C. Soley</H3>
<P>While a few incidents of &quot;political correctness&quot; have received
lavish attention from the mass media, the corporate buyout of academia has gone
nearly unnoticed.  In <I>Leasing the Ivory Tower,</I> Soley exhaustively
documents how corporations, the military, and right-wing foundations have
quietly seized control of our institutions of higher learning. While the news
media have diverted public attention with exaggerated claims of a leftist
takeover of the university, financially strained colleges and universities
working in service of corporations, Soley argues, have dealt a massive betrayal
to the students and taxpayers who pick up the bill. </P>
<P>Award winning writer Lawrence Soley gives the dirty details on campuses
nationwide, including Columbia, Yale, Harvard, MIT, Michigan State, Johns
Hopkins, University of Arizona, Catholic University, Brigham Young, and
University of California. Impassioned, outraged, and meticulously documented,
<I>Leasing the Ivory Tower</I>  exposes the growing corporate threats to the
future of intellectual inquiry and civil society itself.</P>
<P>Lawrence C. Soley has taught at the University of Alabama, University of
Georgia, Penn State, and the City University of New York.  He currently teaches
at Marquette University in Milwaukee.  Soley's previous books include The <I>News
Shapers </I>(Praeger, 1992),<I>
 Radio Warfare</I> (Praeger, 1989), and
<I>Clandestine Radio Broadcasting</I> (Praeger, 1987), which was selected as
one of the &quot;outstanding&quot; books of 1987 by Choice magazine.  With
Village Voice reporter Marc Cooper, Soley received the prestigious Sigma Delta
Chi Award for a Mother Jones article about the small group of &quot;experts&quot;
repeatedly quoted by television news reporters.  In 1993, Soley and former
Marquette University professor Bob Craig received the American Academy of
Advertising's &quot;Best Article Award&quot; for a research report titled &quot;Advertising
Pressures on Newspapers.&quot; </P>
<P>$13.00 paper, $30.00 cloth</P>
<HR>
<MENU>
<LI>See for yourself. Read an <A HREF="leasEXC.HTM">
excerpt</A> of
<I>Leasing the Ivory Tower</I></LI></MENU>
