it: You type in short commands to navigate through directories and get or
put files. FTP is built in to most web browsers (though not all browsers
can send files -- you'll need a dedicated FTP program for that).

<ul>
<li><b><a
href="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/ftp-list/faq/faq.ht
ml">Anonymous FTP FAQ</a></b>
</ul>

<P>For Windows users LOL also provides an excellent FTP tool, called
CuteFTP, via the LOL <!--HREF HERE-->Internet Page. MAC Users can get a
comparable tool
from the LOL/ShareWorld Mac file library. Please consult the
instructions within LOL and your FTP programm's help system for more
information.

<a name="m"> </a>
<P><b>Mailing lists</b> are a special application of e-mail: You send an
e-mail message to a "listserver" (a specially configured machine) asking to
