<title>Organization Services</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#72203A" link="#0001FF">

<p><img src="images/swlogo.gif" width="546" height="134"
naturalsizeflag="0"></p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td align="center" valign="top" width="22%"><a
        href="swhome.htm"><img src="images/wel.gif" border="0"
        width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        <a href="sub.htm"><img src="images/subserv.gif"
        border="0" width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        <a href="org.htm"><img src="images/orgon.gif" border="0"
        width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        &nbsp;<a href="part.htm"><img src="images/part.gif"
        border="0" width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        <a href="faq.htm"><img src="images/faq.gif" border="0"
        width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        <a href="memb.htm"><img src="images/members.gif"
        border="0" width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        <a href="staff.htm"><img src="images/staff.gif"
        border="0" width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        <a href="join.htm"><img src="images/join.gif" border="0"
        width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a></td>
        <td align="center" valign="top" width="2%"><img
        src="images/line.gif" align="texttop" width="10"
        height="720" naturalsizeflag="2" valign="TOP"><br>
        </td>
        <td valign="top" width="76%">&nbsp;<img
        src="images/orgban.gif" width="343" height="14"
        naturalsizeflag="0"> <p>Any socially progressive
        organization can participate in ShareWorld either by
        sponsoring a members-only Web system or providing content
        to appear on the ShareWorld community of systems. </p>
        <p>National and regional non-profit organizations,
        educational organizations, political action groups,
        grassroots lobbying groups, associations, and socially
        responsible businesses are all welcome to sponsor a
        private members-only ShareWorld Web system. There are no
        up-front fees and no financial risk to the organization.
        All you need is: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>A focused progressive topic or issue for which
                the organization campaigns.</li>
            <li>A substantial membership base that you wish to
                expand.</li>
            <li>Loyal activist members with whom you wish to
                interact more regularly.</li>
            <li>Time and effort to work with us on developing and
                maintaining provocative content areas geared to
                the interests of your members.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>&nbsp; </p>
        <h3>What a Sponsoring Organization Gets From ShareWorld </h3>
        <p>When an organization joins ShareWorld by sponsoring a
        members-only Web system, the organization benefits in the
        following ways : </p>
        <ul>
            <li>ShareWorld builds a highly interactive Web System
                tailored to the needs of the organization.<br>
                </li>
            <li>ShareWorld, through its promotion efforts, gets
                the organization's members online.<br>
                </li>
            <li>The organization can now interact with their
                constituents or clients on a day-to-day basis,
                allowing for grassroots lobbying, online activism,
                polling, fundraising, sales, and all types of
                communications.<br>
                </li>
            <li>Members of the organization have an increased
                identification and connection within your
                community. <br>
                </li>
            <li>The organization gets ongoing revenue for every
                member remaining online.<br>
                </li>
            <li>The organization and its members become part of a
                larger progressive online community with access
                to a wide array of interactive content, people,
                and resources.<br>
                </li>
            <li>Organization staff can utilize the strength of
                the Internet and the flexible tools of ShareWorld
                for internal communications purposes, including
                staff-only policy forums, calendars of events,
                and chat groups.<br>
                </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What ShareWorld Costs a Sponsoring Organization </h3>
        <p>NOTHING. ShareWorld pays for everything, including: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Creating the members-only Web system, and a
                public Web site if the organization does not
                already have one.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Software, hardware, and custom programming needed
                to create and maintain the Web systems.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Marketing directly to the organization's members
                through a variety of direct marketing, print, and
                electronic mediums.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><i>The organization does, however, need to devote time
        towards the initial creation and regular updating of
        organization-specific content. The more effort devoted to
        enhancing the content (e.g. news updates, finding experts
        to teach an online course, creating a timely forum), the
        more likely your members will stay online and participate
        in the community.</i> </p>
        <p>&nbsp; </p>
        <h3>How Does an Organization Sponsor Their Own Members-Only
        Web System? </h3>
        <p>When an organization decides to join ShareWorld by
        sponsoring a members-only system, the following happens: </p>
        <ol>
            <li>With help from the organization's staff,
                ShareWorld will, at our expense, create a
                members-only Web system crafted to the organization's
                needs, and consistent with other ShareWorld
                systems.</li>
            <li>ShareWorld will train a staff member at the
                organization how to revise and update
                organization specific online content on a regular basis.</li>
            <li>ShareWorld will create a marketing plan with the
                organization that will most effectively reach
                members interested in joining the organization's
                online community.</li>
            <li>ShareWorld will go forward with the promotion
                plan at ShareWorld's expense in an effort to
                bring online as many of the organization's
                members as possible within the first six months
                of system operation.</li>
            <li>ShareWorld will donate to the organization $10
                for every ShareWorld and Unlimited Internet
                Access Bundle subscriber, and $1.00 per month for
                each ShareWorld subscriber, after the subscriber
                has been a member of ShareWorld for 90 days.
                Prodigy Internet will also help support the
                organization by contributing $1 per month, after
                3 months, for every member for as long as the member
                maintains their Prodigy Internet account.</li>
        </ol>
        <h3>What's The Next Step? </h3>
        <p>For more information about sponsoring a members-only
        Web system on ShareWorld, or about participating in the
        ShareWorld community, please call George Cigale at
        617/629-4500, or e-mail to <a
        href="mailto:gcigale@sharegroup.com">gcigale@sharegroup.com.</a>
        You can get a test run of a sample ShareWorld system by
        clicking on JOIN on the left side of this page. </p>
        <p align="center"><a href="org.htm"><img
        src="images/top.gif" border="0" width="192" height="14"></a> </p>
        <p align="center"><br>
        </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

