        <a href="staff.htm"><img src="images/staff.gif"
        border="0" width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a><br>
        <a href="join.htm"><img src="images/join.gif" border="0"
        width="84" height="56" naturalsizeflag="0"></a></td>
        <td align="center" valign="top" width="2%"><img
        src="images/line.gif" align="texttop" width="10"
        height="720" naturalsizeflag="2" valign="TOP"><br>
        <br>
        </td>
        <td valign="top" width="76%">&nbsp;<img
        src="images/qa.gif" width="419" height="14"
        naturalsizeflag="0"> <p><b><i>What is ShareWorld?</i></b> </p>
        <p>ShareWorld is many things to a variety people and
        organizations. To read about the specific services we
        offer to individual subscribers and client organizations,
        please choose the relevant buttons on the left. To
        summarize, ShareWorld does the following: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Helps non-profit organizations (e.g. The
                Wilderness Society) and socially responsible
                businesses (e.g. The Nation) get online with no financial
                expenditures or risk.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Creates customized public and members-only Web
                systems for progressive organizations.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Markets the online service directly to the
                organizations' members in order to bring their
                members and customers onto the Internet to form a
                progressive online community.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Develops content areas targeted to the interests
                of the progressive community, linking individual
                members of the various organizations through
                interaction in areas such as Forums, the Online
                School, and the Socially Responsible Store. </li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Subscribers pay a monthly fee to ShareWorld for
                access to the organizations' members-only Web
                systems and ShareWorld content areas. A
                significant portion of the fees is contributed
                directly to the subscriber's organization. The
                participating organizations are therefore
                benefiting from a substantial revenue stream with
                no financial risk incurred. Our subscribers
                appreciate that their online spending is
                benefiting the causes and organizations about
                which they care deeply.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><b><i>What does it cost an organization to join
        ShareWorld?</i></b> </p>
        <p>NOTHING. ShareWorld pays for: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Creating the members-only Web system, and the
                public Web site if the organization does not have
                one.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Software, hardware, and custom programming needed
                to create and maintain the Web systems.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Promoting directly to the organization's members
                through a variety of direct marketing, print, and
                electronic mediums.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>The organization does, however, need to devote
                time towards the initial creation and regular
                updating of content. The more effort devoted to
                enhancing the content (e.g. news updates, finding
                experts to teach an online course, creating a
                timely forum), the more likely your members will
                stay online and participate in the community.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><b><i>What are the benefits for an organization
        joining ShareWorld?</i></b> </p>
        <p>When an organization joins ShareWorld by sponsoring
        their own online members-only Web system, the
        organization benefits in the following ways : </p>
        <ul>
            <li>ShareWorld builds a highly interactive
                members-only Web System tailored to the needs of
                the organization.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>ShareWorld, through its promotion efforts, gets
                the organization's members online.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>The organization can now interact with their
                constituents or clients on a day to day basis,
                allowing for grassroots lobbying, online activism,
                polling, fundraising, sales, and all types of
                communications.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Members of the organization have an increased
                identification and connection within your
                community. </li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>The organization gets ongoing revenue for every
                member remaining online.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>The organization and its members become part of a
                larger progressive online community with access
                to a wide array of interactive content, people,
                and resources.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Organization staff can utilize the strength of
                the Internet and the flexible tools of ShareWorld
                for internal communications purposes, including
                staff-only policy forums, calendars of events,
                and chat groups.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><b><i>What does ShareWorld cost an individual
        subscriber?</i></b> </p>
        <p><i>ShareWorld Member Fees <br>
        <br>
        </i>ShareWorld's monthly subscription fee is $8. When you
        join any of the ShareWorld members-only systems, you get
        a user ID and password and then have unlimited access to
        all members-only ShareWorld areas listed above as well as
        to the specific content areas provided by the sponsoring organization
        you are supporting. <br>
        <br>
        The sponsoring organization of your system will receive
        $1 of your monthly subscription to benefit their
        campaigns, allowing the organizations to spend less time
        fundraising and more time on their mission. <br>
        <br>
        Users can also join additional private systems beyond the
        first (which costs $8 a month) for only $2 a month, half
        of which goes to the new sponsoring organization. <i><br>
        <br>
        Internet Access Fees <br>
        <br>
        </i>If you require Internet access, or want to switch to
        a reliable low cost provider and help benefit your
        participating organization by doing so, please consider
        Prodigy Internet. For ShareWorld members, Prodigy offers
        unlimited access, exceptional services, and no startup or
        software fees. For a monthly rate of $19.95 per month,
        you get unlimited local-call Web access, including space
        for your own personal web page. <br>
        <br>
        The sponsoring organizations will receive $10 after you
        use Prodigy Internet for 3 months, and $1 per month of
        your ongoing internet fees for as long as you maintain
        your Prodigy account. To benefit your favorite organizations,
        you must make the transition from your current provider
        to Prodigy once you join a ShareWorld system. </p>
        <p><b><i>Why is it worth it?</i></b> </p>
        <p>As a ShareWorld subscriber, you get access to a
        members-only Web system with loads of interactive content
        areas and at the same time, you also benefit an
        organization of your choosing and the overall project of bringing
        the progressive world online and together. </p>
        <p><b><i>Can I try it out first?</i></b> </p>
        <p>Absolutely. Click on join and follow the instructions.
        You can try out any ShareWorld system for 3 hours or 15
        days, whichever comes first, before incurring any
        expense. </p>
        <p><b><i>How do I join?</i></b> </p>
        <p>Click on the JOIN button on the left, and follow the
        instruction, also listed below. </p>
        <p>STEP 1: Test drive a ShareWorld members-only system by
        choosing one of the organizations below. All of them
        share many of the ShareWorld content areas, but each has
        some unique content provided solely for members of the
        organization's online system. You won't be able to access everything,
        but you will get a very good feel for what is available. </p>
        <p>STEP 2: Decide to join because the content areas,
        member interaction, and community is worth the 8 bucks
        each month. Especially since a part of the $8 will go
        directly to the sponsoring organization to pay for their campaigns. </p>
        <p>STEP 3: Come back here and click on JOIN, or click on
        JOIN in the top menu bar during your test drive of a
        system. You will then get some more information to make
        sure you know exactly what you are getting, and if you decide
        to proceed you will be asked for your credit card
        information for payment, and will be allowed 3 free hours
        or 15 free days to check everything out before being
        billed. You will not be billed until you go beyond the
        allotted free time. </p>
        <p>STEP 4: Become an active member of a growing
        progressive online community. Participate in a friendly
        and thoughtful environment through forums, school
        courses, book clubs, and other interactive areas. </p>
        <p><b><i>How do I navigate around ShareWorld?</i></b> </p>
        <p>ShareWorld systems have a common look and feel. You
        will never lose your way on the Internet because the
        graphical Menu Bar at the top, and the Table of Contents
        frame at the left of your screen will stay with you as you
        browse. This allows you to go out to the far reaches of
        the Internet, and get back to your favorite ShareWorld
        locations with one click of the mouse. When you click on
        a Menu Bar option at the top (e.g. Messages), the Table
        of Contents frame will show you the options available in
        that area (e.g. E-Mail, Forums, Teleconferencing, Help).
        Then you can click on the item of your choice (e.g.
        Forums) to go to that content area in the large frame.
        Try it out -- we think you'll find it easy to use and
        efficient. </p>
        <p><b><i>How do I contact ShareWorld staff?</i></b> </p>
        <p>For technical support on using the content areas of
        ShareWorld system, please e-mail <a
        href="mailto://support@shareworld.com">support@shareworld.com </a>after
        giving the help and tutorial screens a shot. </p>
        <p>For technical support regarding your Internet access
        or software problems, please call your Internet Service
        Provider. Our preferred provider is Prodigy Internet. If
        your account is with Prodigy, call 800/776-3449 or e-mail <a
        href="http://www.prodigy.com/">support@prodigy.com</a>. </p>
        <p>To become a member of ShareWorld, click on JOIN (to
        the left). You will also be able to call an 800 number in
        the near future to sign up.</p>
        <p>To contact ShareWorld about anything else: </p>
        <p>ShareWorld Online Communities</p>
        <p>58 Day St. </p>
        <p>Somerville, MA 02144 </p>
        <p>617/629-4500 Phone </p>
        <p>617/629-4510 Fax </p>
        <address>
            <a href="mailto:gcigale@sharegroup.com">gcigale@sharegroup.com </a>
        </address>
        <p>We welcome feedback, suggestions for creative content
        areas, offers to participate in the development of the
        community, inquiries on how to sponsor your
        organization's own system, and just generally interesting conversations. </p>
        <p><b><i>Do I need new software to use ShareWorld?</i></b> </p>
        <p>No. You can access ShareWorld using any Web Browser
        that supports frames, though we highly recommend the
        latest versions of <a href="http://www.microsoft.com">Microsoft Explorer</a>
        and <a href="http://www.netscape.com">Netscape Navigator</a>,
        available for download from each company's Web site.
        ShareWorld includes some additional interactive capabilities
        currently only available to Windows users. These are
        &quot;plug-ins&quot; that will be downloaded to your
        system if you choose to do so. For more information on
        plug-ins, consult the Help area within a ShareWorld
        system. </p>
        <p><b><i>Do I need new Internet access to use ShareWorld?</i></b> </p>
        <p>If you're reading this, you already have Internet
        access, and with a frame-ready browser, you are ready to
        join ShareWorld. We do, however, encourage you to try
        Prodigy's nation-wide Internet Access. Prodigy offers two
        rate plans, including unlimited access at a very competitive
        rate. Furthermore, a portion of your payments to Prodigy
        will go towards funding your sponsoring organization's
        efforts. If you want to make the switch or need
        additional info, click here: <a href="prodigy.htm">Prodigy</a>.</p>
        <p><b><i>How does ShareWorld choose sponsoring
        organizations to be part of the ShareWorld Online
        Communities?</i></b> </p>
        <p>All socially progressive organizations are eligible to
        participate in ShareWorld either by sponsoring a
        members-only Web system, providing content created by the
        organization to appear on ShareWorld systems, or both. </p>
        <p>National and regional non-profit organizations,
        educational organizations, political action groups,
        grassroots lobbying groups, associations, and socially
        responsible businesses are all potentially welcome to
        sponsor a private members-only ShareWorld Web system.
        There are no up-front fees and no financial risk to the
        organization. All you need is: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>A focused progressive topic or issue for which
                the organization campaigns.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A substantial membership base that you wish to
                expand.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Loyal activist members with whom you wish to
                interact more regularly.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Time and effort to work with us on developing and
                maintaining interesting content areas geared to
                the interests of your members.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Organizations that apply are chosen for having their
        own system based on a variety of factors including
        whether their memberships are large enough to sustain the
        costs. </p>
        <p><em><strong>How are sponsoring organizations involved
        in ShareWorld?</strong></em> </p>
        <p>When an organization is accepted to join ShareWorld by
        sponsoring a members-only system, the following happens: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>With help from the organization's staff,
                ShareWorld will, at ShareWorld's expense, create
                a members-only Web system crafted to the
                organization's needs, and consistent with other
                ShareWorld systems.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>ShareWorld will train a staff member at the
                organization how to revise and update online
                content on a regular basis.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>ShareWorld will create a marketing plan with the
                organization that will most effectively reach
                members that will be interested in joining the
                organization's online community.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>ShareWorld will go forward with the marketing
                plan at ShareWorld's expense in an effort to
                bring online as many of the organization's
                members as possible within the first six months
                of marketing.</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>ShareWorld will donate to the organization $10
                for every ShareWorld and Unlimited Internet
                Access Bundle subscriber, and $1.00 per month for
                each ShareWorld subscriber, after the subscriber
                has been a member of ShareWorld for 90 days.
                Prodigy Internet will also help support the
                organization by contributing $1 per month, after
                3 months, for every member for as long as the member
                maintains their Prodigy Internet account. </li>
        </ul>
        <p><b><i>How can I help build the ShareWorld Online
        Community?</i></b> </p>
        <p>Join ShareWorld and begin participating in Forums,
        Book Clubs, Online Education, and a variety of other
        areas. If you are a writer, academic, artist, political
        activist, work with progressive organizations, or have a
        great idea for new content areas that can enhance the
        ShareWorld community (e.g. a great online course, new
        forums, sources for job listings), please e-mail us at <a
        href="mailto:gcigale@sharegroup.com">gcigale@sharegroup.com</a>. </p>
        <p><b><i>How do I quit ShareWorld?</i></b> </p>
        <p>If you must quit ShareWorld, please let us know so we
        can improve our services. If you do decide to quit, there
        is a selection to do so in the &quot;Join&quot; section
        of each system. No hassle. Your user ID will be
        deactivated in 3-5 business days. </p>
        <p align="center">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a
        href="faq.htm"><img src="images/top.gif" border="0"
        width="192" height="14"></a> </p>
        <p align="center"><br>
        </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p align="center">&nbsp; </p>
</body>
