<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <h2><font color="#961814"><em>What do you get?</em></font></h2>
        <p>When you join <!--webbot bot="Substitution"
        s-variable="client on line" startspan -->Left On Line<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="17324" --> you
        get:</p>
        <blockquote>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> </font>Membership in the
            community of <!--webbot bot="Substitution"
            s-variable="client on line" startspan -->Left On Line<!--webbot
            bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="17324" -->
            users, interaction with its members, and use of its
            many tools, resources, guides, etc.</p>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> </font>Membership in the
            ShareWorld community, interaction with its members,
            and use of its forums, courses, and other unique
            facilities.</p>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> </font>Internet guidance</p>
        </blockquote>
        <p>To see more details regarding specific <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" -->
        offerings, please consult the <a
        href="http://www.lbbs.org/index.htm" target="_top">ZNet</a>
        or <a
        href="http://www.lol.shareworld.com/share/swhome.htm">ShareWorld</a>
        web sites or examine the <a
        href="http://www.lol.shareworld.com/leftonl/lolvis.htm"><!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --> Visitors
        Site</a>.</p>
        <p>To join now click any of the Join <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="client on line" startspan
        -->Left On Line<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="17324" --> links on this page. (Remember that
        you do need a browser able to handle frames -- <a
        href="http://www.microsoft.com"><font size="2"
        face="Arial"><strong>Microsoft Explorer 3.0</strong></font></a><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong> </strong></font><font
        size="3">or </font><a href="http://www.netscape.com"><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong>Netscape Navigator 3.0</strong></font></a><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong> </strong></font><font
        size="3">are optimal.</font>) To join you will have to
        fil out a subscription form including credit card
        information. Once you are finished you will have full
        access on the spot.</p>
        <p align="center"><a href="http://lbbs.org/newuser"
        target="viewarea"><font size="4"><strong>Join <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="client on line" startspan
        -->Left On Line<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="17324" --></strong></font></a></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="images/redline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <h2><font color="#961814"><em>What does it cost?</em></font></h2>
        <blockquote>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> </font>There is only one fee,
            with no variations: $8 a month for unlimited access. </p>
        </blockquote>
        <p>This includes forums, E-Mail, diverse information
        sources, access to many magazines and to the online
        magazine, <font color="#000000"><em><strong>Marble</strong></em></font>,
        establishing and maintaining your own web site (with
        limits on size), extensive aid in navigating the Web, and
        unlimited use of various other facilities like activism
        online, job banks, the book club, on line games, polls,
        and teleconferencing, etc. Online courses cost extra, but
        are not available to anyone outside ShareWorld.</p>
        <p>When you first join you receive 3 hours or fifteen
        days of free use, whichever you complete first, before
        your monthly billing begins.</p>
        <blockquote>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20">You must have an Internet
            account and access <!--webbot bot="Substitution"
            s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
            bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --> with
            a browser that can handle forms.</font></p>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> If you do not have an
            unlimited Internet account elsewhere we can get you
            one for $20 a month with Prodigy Internet, with whom
            we have a &quot;creative alliance.&quot; They provide
            a very robust and efficient installation package, a
            huge list of dial-up numbers from around the country
            and the world, a full suite of Internet
            functionality, and quite a large store of proprietary
            information content. (They also offer a $10 for 10
            hours monthly account.) Check out the Prodigy Section
            of the Join/Quit Table of Contents for more
            information, please.</font></p>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> Receiving your internet
            access from Prodigy Internet at our initiation is
            very advantageous to us financially and gets you
            exceptional tools specially adjusted to be extra
            useful with our system--however is not mandatory. You
            can use any national or local provider to access <!--webbot
            bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
            bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" -->.</font></p>
        </blockquote>
        <p align="center"><a href="http://lbbs.org/newuser"
        target="viewarea"><font size="4"><strong>Join <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="client on line" startspan
        -->Left On Line<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="17324" --></strong></font></a><font size="4"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></font></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="images/redline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <h2><font color="#961814"><em>Why join?</em></font></h2>
        <blockquote>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> </font>One reason to join is
            to get access to the many and varied resources we
            offer.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> </font>A second reason to
            join is to help support this ambitious project to
            bring the progressive and left community into
            telecommunications visibility. This is also a good
            reason to have us get you a Prodigy/ShareWorld
            Internet access account rather than using some other
            provider for your Internet access.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <p>We know that eight dollars a month (above and beyond
        your Internet access fees, whatever they may be) is not
        an insignificant cost to many users. But developing and
        maintaining a comprehensive and cutting edge
        telecommunications community and helping to finance the
        many diverse activities of the many participating
        organizations is an expensive undertaking and we do not
        have access to large donor support, nor to ad revenues.
        So we must charge users directly and hope that you will
        join in sufficient numbers to allow us to enlarge the
        left and progressive media presence as it deserves. Even
        with all these constraints, pressures, and motives
        pushing up our price, $8 is in line with industry norms
        (Microsoft Network by browser is projected to cost $7,
        for example, and many other serious member-only sites are
        in the $10 range and more).</p>
        <p align="center"><a href="http://lbbs.org/newuser"
        target="viewarea"><font size="4"><strong>Join <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="client on line" startspan
        -->Left On Line<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="17324" --></strong></font></a></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="images/redline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <h2><font color="#961814"><em>How do you join?</em></font></h2>
        <p>Joining is simple. </p>
        <blockquote>
            <p><font size="3"><img src="images/dot.gif"
            width="20" height="20"> </font>Just click the link
            located directly below and then fill out the
            requisite form so we can charge your credit card each
            month, and you are a member. </p>
        </blockquote>
        <p>It happens online, on the spot. You can discontinue
        your membership at any time, of course, by going to the
        Join or Users sections of <!--webbot bot="Substitution"
        s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --> and
        choosing Quit and following instructions. There are no
        refunds for prior fees paid.</p>
        <p>If you do not have a credit card, in the future you
        will be able to join for 6 months at a time, for a fee of
        $50, or for a year at a time, for a fee of $100, by
        sending a check with the user ID you would like to have
        on the system (usually one's name, adapted a bit to be
        unique) and a password (4 to 9 characters).</p>
        <p align="center"><a href="http://lbbs.org/newuser"
        target="viewarea"><font size="4"><strong>Join <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="client on line" startspan
        -->Left On Line<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="17324" --></strong></font></a><font size="4"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></font></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>
