naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p align="left"><font color="#800000" size="5"><em><strong>Forums
        and Teleconferencing Center</strong></em></font></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p align="left"><img src="redline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p align="left"><font size="3">The Forum/NewsGroup &amp;
        Teleconference Center of <!--webbot bot="Substitution"
        s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --><strong> </strong>are
        where members write messages which anyone using the
        system can read and reply to so that discussions
        accumulate. All of our Forums are mediated, and many are
        led by members knowledgable in the subject area. Typical
        Internet News Groups are public and not nearly so civil
        and substantive as our home grown kind.</font></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p align="left"><img src="redline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p align="left"><font color="#800000" size="3"><em><strong>Basic
        Forum Info</strong></em></font><font color="#0000FF"
        size="3" face="Arial"><strong><br>
        </strong></font><font size="3">Here is a partical list of
        topics and areas of concern that have forums: current
        events, mass media, ecology, humor, feminism, life
        styles, sexuality, books, anarchy, activism, labor
        issues, general philosophy, third parties, shopping tips,
        marxism, law, veganism, youth, campus politics, foreign
        policy, media politics, gender, history, markets,
        economic vision, political economy, popular culture,
        progressive publications, race, religion, education, the
        right wing...</font></p>
        <p align="left"><font size="3">We are also developing
        forums where noted scholars in various fields converse
        and answer questions, etc., including our first,
        ChomskyChat, where the special participant is Noam
        Chomsky.</font></p>
        <p align="left"><font size="3">Many forums sponsored by <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --> are also
        available to other ShareWorld systems, and, vice versa,
        forums sponsored by other ShareWorld systems are
        available to <!--webbot bot="Substitution"
        s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --> members.</font></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p align="left"><img src="redline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p><font color="#800000" size="3"><em><strong>Do It Easy</strong></em></font><font
        color="#0000FF" size="3" face="Arial"><strong><br>
        </strong></font>Once you are a member, you can access <font
        size="3"><!--webbot bot="Substitution" s-variable="col"
        startspan -->LOL<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="538" --> forums within your browser window.</font>
        You click a link and see a list of available forums. You
        click one forum and read messages, write a new message,
        or write replies. It is very easy but lacks more
        sophisticated functionality such as searching, storing
        messages, etc. that you get when you use a News Reader.
        However, this option is also available within <font
        size="3"><!--webbot bot="Substitution" s-variable="col"
        startspan -->LOL<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="538" --></font> as our forums, along with all
        News Groups, are also avaulable to our users via Netscape
        Navigator's News Reader, Microsoft Explororer's News
        Reader, or any other commerical News Reader you might
        prefer to use.</p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="redline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p><font color="#800000" size="3"><em><strong>Teleconferencing</strong></em></font><font
        color="#0000FF" size="3" face="Arial"><strong><br>
        </strong></font><font color="#000000" size="3"><strong><!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --></strong></font>
        also has extensive teleconferencing capacities, soon to
        be augmented with audio capabilities. As with Forum work,
        you can do your teleconferencing right in your browser
        window or typical chat client programs.. </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p align="center"><a
        href="http://www.lol.shareworld.com/leftonl/visitabout.htm"><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong>Return to About LOL's
        Features </strong></font></a></p>
        <p align="center"><a
        href="http://www.lol.shareworld.com/leftonl/lolvis.htm"><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong>Return to About LOL</strong></font></a></p>
    </blockquote>
