<body background="images/greback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
link="#FF0000" vlink="#FF0000" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0">

<p><img src="images/greline.gif" width="432" height="4"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p><img src="images/rcenter.jpg" width="400" height="181"
        naturalsizeflag="2"></p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="images/grewel.gif" width="432" height="30"
naturalsizeflag="3"></p>

<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p>The World Wide Web is a very powerful tool for all
        types of research. There is an almost endless store of
        information, but finding what you need can be difficult
        and time consuming.</p>
        <p><!--webbot bot="Substitution" s-variable="col"
        startspan -->LOL<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="538" -->'s Research Area brings together
        several resources for conducting serious, as well as
        leisurely research. We offer a number of links that help
        you find information on a variety of topics, within <!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" -->,
        ShareWorld Online Communities, other progressive
        resources (such as IGC -- the Institute for Global
        Communications), and the Web in general. These tools are
        all available to members only.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Search <!--webbot bot="Substitution"
                s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
                bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" -->
                provides a tool for finding materials within our
                system, including sophisticated search options.</li>
            <li>Ask Experts links to a list of forums where
                people who are expert in different fields are
                willing to try to answer your questions.</li>
            <li>Search IGC provides a tool for finding materials
                within the entire IGC (PeaceNet, EcoNet,
                LaborNet, Women's Net) universe, including
                sophisticated search options.</li>
            <li>Related forums leads to links to forums with <!--webbot
                bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
                bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" -->
                and ShareWorld where people discuss research
                issues, methods/tips, and problems.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The rest of the links in the Research TOC (that would
        appear to the left, if you were in the member only
        system, are to diverse sites and locales offerings
        particular research facilities. For example, </p>
        <ul>
            <li>library tools</li>
            <li>a News Group Search Engine</li>
            <li>a way to look up people's E-Mail address
                throughout the internet</li>
            <li>book resources</li>
            <li>music lyric resources</li>
            <li>links to list of periodicals, newspapers, etc.</li>
            <li>Government resources</li>
            <li>computer research resources</li>
            <li>the NY Times online</li>
            <li>the Noam Chomsky Archive, which is also a part of <!--webbot
                bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
                bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" -->.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><!--webbot bot="Substitution" s-variable="col"
        startspan -->LOL<!--webbot bot="Substitution" endspan
        i-checksum="538" --> also has a Web Guide section which
        includes tools for searching the World Wide Web and
        Internet and advice on and reviews of recommended sites,
        and our News section which includes a variety of News
        resource tools and links.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p align="center"><a
        href="http://www.lol.shareworld.com/leftonl/visitabout.htm"><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong>Return to About</strong></font><font
        size="1" face="Arial"><strong> </strong></font><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong><!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" -->'s
        Features</strong></font></a><font size="2" face="Arial"><strong> </strong></font></p>
        <p align="center"><a
        href="http://www.lol.shareworld.com/leftonl/lolvis.htm"><font
        size="2" face="Arial"><strong>Return to </strong></font><font
        size="1" face="Arial"><strong><!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" s-variable="col" startspan -->LOL<!--webbot
        bot="Substitution" endspan i-checksum="538" --> Visitor's
        Top Page</strong></font></a></p>
