<title>Banking Practice</title>
<body background="linen.gif" text="000000" link="2F4F2F" vlink="A62A2A">
<center>
<img src="lprh_grn.gif">
<br>
<br>
<B>LOCKE PURNELL RAIN HARRELL</B><br>
<B>(A Professional Corporation)</B><br>
<P><u><B>BANKING PRACTICE</u></B><br>
</center>
<p>  
	Locke Purnell Rain Harrell has an extensive Banking practice,
having represented major banks and bank holding companies, as well as smaller independent
banks, in all aspects of its operations.  We represent banks and other institutional lenders in
numerous commercial lending and finance transactions locally and nationally.  <p>

<h3>Commercial and Corporate Lending</h3><p>

     We have been very active in middle-market and large corporate line-of-credit and project
financings.  In addition to single-lender transactions, we have significant experience representing
agents in multi-bank loans and in loan participations.  We have broad experience in transactions
involving credit enhanced securitization transactions and in specialized lending areas such as
ESOP financings.  We actively participate in asset-based lending, mezzanine financing, and
subordinated and senior debt financing for nationally announced leveraged buy outs.<p>

<h3>Consumer Lending</h3><p>

     Our staff includes attorneys experienced in truth-in-lending, usury and other laws
pertaining to consumer loans.<p>

<h3>General Finance/Capital Markets</h3><p>

     We represent underwriters and placement agents in both debt and equity financings, and
have experience in structured finance transactions as well as credit-enhanced tax-exempt and
taxable debt financings.<p>

<h3>Regulatory Matters</h3><p>

     We have served as counsel in numerous bank acquisitions and mergers, including
representation of RepublicBank in many of its subsidiary bank acquisitions and in its 1987
merger with InterFirst Bank, including the complex tax planning for that merger.  Our banking
attorneys closely monitor the effects of the FIRREA legislation and its local affect and are
experienced in bank and thrift regulatory matters.  We have filed "de novo" national bank
charter applications and presented formal oppositions to pending applications.<p>

<h3>Trustee Representation</h3><p>

     Numerous members of our Tax group continuously work with individuals and bank trust
departments in formulating personal estate plans.  Our Banking group
represents banks and trustees in the administration of trust assets and trustee's duties in corporate
debt financings.  We have experience in the Trust Indenture Act of 1939.<p>

<h3>Workouts and Restructurings</h3><p>

     During the 1970s and 1980s, our Real Estate, Bankruptcy and Litigation groups
developed broad-based experience in workouts and problem loans, having been involved in
major loan workouts on behalf of our real estate lending clients.  Our Real Estate group often
works closely with our Litigation and Bankruptcy groups on workouts and problem loans. 
Initially, our litigation and bankruptcy attorneys may help plan strategy or assist in negotiations. 
If a successful workout does not occur, our litigators may be called upon to seize rents, have
a receiver appointed, quash a temporary restraining order, obtain an injunction or exercise other
lender's remedies.

</DOC>
