<TITLE>m-estate.htm </TITLE>
<BODY background="linen.gif" text="000000" link="2F4F2F" vlink="A62A2A">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="lprh_grn.gif">

<P><B>LOCKE PURNELL RAIN HARRELL</B>
<BR><B>(A Professional Corporation)</B>
<P><B><U>ESTATE PLANNING AND ADMINISTRATION</U></B>
</CENTER>
<P> Seven attorneys at Locke Purnell Rain Harrell are involved in the estate planning and estate
administration practice.  The firm's estate planning practice includes, but is not limited to, the
preparation of wills, codicils, inter vivos trusts, testamentary trusts, disability planning
documents, various types of insurance trusts, family limited partnerships, personal residence
trusts, education trusts, and charitable lead and remainder trusts.  The firm's estate planning
group is also experienced in counseling clients about current estate and gift tax planning
opportunities, asset protection, family wealth transition and business succession plans.  The
firm's estate administration practice involves guiding the administration of estates ranging from
small, non-taxable estates to multi-million dollar estates of U.S. citizens and non-citizens with
assets throughout the United States and abroad, and includes the preparation of federal estate tax
returns and state inheritance and estate tax returns.  This group has handled numerous will
contests, trust construction matters and estate and trust litigation, as well as gift and estate tax
audits and valuation controversies with the Internal Revenue Service and other taxing authorities. 
The estate planning and administration group is also involved in the legal aspects of transferring
title to estate assets (including mineral interests) to beneficiaries.
<HR>
<CENTER>
<P><B>ESTATE AND TAX PLANNING</B>
<P><B><U>REPRESENTATIVE CLIENTS AND TRANSACTIONS</U></B>
</CENTER>
<P> Listed below are some of the family businesses and in certain cases publicly-held
corporations where we have represented either the business or family members in estate and tax
planning during the last few years.  In many of these situations we have rendered these services
in matters similar to those for which you have requested this proposal.  
<UL>
<P> 1. Mary Kay Ash and Richard R. Rogers - Mary Kay Cosmetics, Inc.;
<P> 2. Children of Clint Murchison, Jr., Deceased, and their descendants - Roma Corporation
(&quot;Tony Roma&quot;);
<P> 3. Edwin L. Cox - Cox Oil Company;
<P> 4. Mary Anne Sammons Cree - Sammons Enterprises, Inc.;
<P> 5. Phil Simpson (Chief Executive Officer of Republic Gypsum Company) -Republic
Gypsum Company;
<P> 6. J. McDonald Williams - Trammell Crow Company;
<P> 7. Francis Winn - Computer Language Research, Inc. (&quot;Fast Tax&quot;);
<P> 8. James Moroney - A.H. Belo Corporation;
<P> 9. Joe C. Thompson, Jr. - The Florida Company;
<P> 10. Bryan Coca-Cola Bottling Co. (Bryan, Texas);
<P> 11. Ellis M. Skinner, Sr. - Skinner Tile Company;
<P> 12. Fitzhugh Family - Central Beverage;
<P> 13. The McCann Family - Continental Battery Company;
<P> 14. Dunigan Enterprises, Inc. (Abilene, Texas);
<P> 15. Penson and Penn Families - Penn Resources, Inc.;
<P> 16. Ric Middlekauff - Middlekauff Ford;
<P> 17. Mike Bailey - Bailey Red Bird Mazda/Bailey Pontiac;
<P> 18. Carl Westcott - Westcott Ford;
<P> 19. Widow and children of Henry Butts - Butts Oldsmobile;
<P> 20. Ed Doran and family - Doran Chevrolet;
