including, by way of example, staff privileges, discrimination claims, and benefits.
<P><B>Phyllis Guin Cancienne</B>
<BR>Ms. Cancienne practices in the firm's Labor and Employment law group as well as the
Litigation group.  She has experience in litigation of employment claims on behalf of employers
in state and federal courts and administrative agencies, including the Equal Employment
Opportunity Commission, the Louisiana Commission on Human Rights and the Louisiana Civil
Service Commission.  She assists health care clients on a wide range of employment law matters,
including developing personnel policies and employee/staff handbooks, drafting employment
contracts, and counseling regarding hiring and retention.  Ms. Cancienne is also a frequent
lecturer on employment law issues in the health care arena.
