<TR>
<TD ALIGN=TOP >

<P>ALSO AVAILABLE: ENVIRONMENTAL LAW BULLETINS ON THE FOLLOWING
SUBJECTS:

<P>1.The lead-based paint disclosure requirements that became effective on September 1, 1996
that are applicable to sale and lease transactions involving residential dwellings built prior to
1978; the status of the regulation of lead-based paint activities.

<P>2.The impact of the new OSHA regulations on the management of asbestos-containing
materials in private sector buildings.

<P>3.Texas environmental laws impacting real estate development: the new Voluntary Cleanup
Program; the new Texas Spill Response Rules; the current Risk Reduction Rules governing
remediation projects in Texas and their proposed amendments; and the little known regulation
(effective in May 1995) requiring alternative tests to determine the presence of a closed landfill
prior to the development of more than one acre of land.
</TABLE>

