<h1>
<center>
Overview of the Low-Income Housing Tax Credit</h1>
<p>
<h3>by CYNTHIA L. BAST</h3>
</center>
<p>

Ms. Bast is an associate in the Austin office of Locke Purnell Rain Harrell.  While she
practices
generally in the corporate and securities area, she has spent the last four years representing
various
clients utilizing the low-income housing tax credit, including developers, non-profit
organizations,
and Texas' only state-wide tax credit syndicator.  Ms. Bast received a B.A. in Economics,
<i>magna
cum laude</i>,  and an M.B.A. from the University of Tulsa and a J.D. with <i>honors</i> from
the
University
of Texas. <p>
</center>
<dt>
<dl><h2>TABLE OF CONTENTS</h2>
<h4>
<p>
<dd>
<dl>
<dt>     OVERVIEW OF THE LOW-INCOME HOUSING TAX CREDIT<p>

<a href="#I">
I.   Legislative Background and History of the Low-Income Housing Tax Credit</a>
