<center>

<P><B>ANTHONY CAMPBELL</B>
</center>
<P><B>ASSOCIATE</B>

<BR><B>Intellectual Property</B>

<P><B><I>Practice Areas</I></B>
<UL TYPE=SQUARE>
<P> <B><LI>Patents, including prosecution, opinions and litigation, with a particular emphasis
on telecommunications, semiconductor and electromagnetic technologies

<P><LI>Trademarks, including prosecution, enforcement and litigation, with substantial
experience in Internet domain disputes, advertising and product packaging

<P><LI>Cyberlaw and technology, emphasizing intangible media, particularly Internet,
multimedia, computer software, hardware and network issues

<P><LI>Marketing and emerging companies, including confidentiality, non-compete,
non-disclosure, syndication and franchising 

<P><LI>Counseling regarding patents, trademarks, copyrights, trade secrets, unfair competition,
and licensing of patents, trademarks, copyrights and trade secrets
</UL>
<P> 

<P><B><I>Education</I></B>

<P>  
<UL TYPE=SQUARE>
<P><LI>  J.D., <B>The University of Texas</B>, 1993
