<center><b> C. BRIAN CASSIDY</center></b><p>
<p>
<b> SHAREHOLDER<p>
Regulatory and Administrative Law/Commercial Litigation<p>
<p>
<i>Practice Areas</i><p>
</b><p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Substantial experience in:</i> <p>
<p>
<b> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
Representation of clients in all types of administrative proceedings, including
contested evidentiary hearings, rulemakings, enforcement actions, permitting
and licensing matters, and judicial review of agency actions.  <p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
Representation of clients in matters involving many different agencies, including
the Public Utility Commission; Texas Natural Resource Conservation
Commission; Railroad Commission of Texas; Texas Workers Compensation
Commission; Texas Commission on Alcohol and Drug Abuse; Texas High-Speed
Rail Authority; Comptroller of Public Accounts; Texas Real Estate Commission;
and the State Board of Public Accountancy.  <p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
Litigation involving commercial uses of real property, municipal annexations
and other governmental actions, and disputes arising from commercial
transactions.  <p>
</b><p>
<i><b> Education</b></i><p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> 
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
</b>J.D., <i>with honors</i>, <b> University of Texas School of Law</b>, 1986 <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> 
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
</b>B.S., <i>with distinction</i>, <b> University of Arizona</b>, 1983 <p>
<p>
<i><b> Specialization</i></b><p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> 
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
</b>Board Certified in Administrative Law by the Texas Board of Legal Specialization <p>
<p>
<i><b> Civic and Professional</i></b><p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;State Bar of Texas (Member, Administrative and Public Law; Environmental and
Natural Resources Law; and Public Utility Law Sections) <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> 
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
</b>Travis County Bar Association (Member, Administrative Law and Real Estate Law
Sections) <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> 
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
</b>Fellow, Texas Bar Foundation <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> 
<!-- WP Style Open:  -->*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<!-- WP Style End:  -->
</b>Member, Real Estate Council of Austin, Inc. <p>
<p>
<i><b> Presentations</i></b><p>
<p>
