<!-- WP Comment LAST UPDATE 5/96 -->
<center><b> CARLYLE H. CHAPMAN, JR.</center></b><p>
<p>
<b> SHAREHOLDER<p>
Labor and Employment/Litigation<p>
<p>
<p>
<i>Practice Areas</b></i><p>
<p>
<i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Representing management and employers in all aspects of labor and employment law
with such industries as insurance, banking, and services. In addition, Mr. Chapman is an
experienced casualty defense trial attorney.  Mr. Chapman has substantial experience in:<p>
</i><p>
<b> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Litigation of employment claims in behalf of employers in state and federal
courts; including claims relating to employment discrimination under state
and federal statutes, workers' compensation laws, ERISA and claims pursued
before state and federal agencies, including the Texas Human Rights
Commission and the Equal Employment Opportunities Commission; <p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employment practices and policies; <p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Advice and counseling regarding employment issues faced by management;  <p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Traditional management labor law; and <p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Preventive employment law through counseling and advice. <p>
</b><p>
<b> <i>Education</b></i><p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;J.D.,<i></i> <b> The University of Michigan</b>, 1973 <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;B.A., Government (Honors), <b> Indiana University</b>, 1970 <p>
<p>
<b> <i>Specialization</b></i><p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Board Certified, Personal Injury Trial Law, Texas Board of Legal
Specialization <p>
