<hr>
<p>

<center><b> JAMES W. CHECKLEY, JR.</center></b><p>
<p>
<b> SHAREHOLDER</b><p>
<b> Administrative Law/Environmental/Public Utility</b><p>
<p>
<b> <i>Practice Areas</i></b><p>
<p>
<b>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Administrative and Regulatory</i> - Practice before state and federal agencies; including
contested hearings and rulemakings, judicial review of agency decisions, and original
judicial proceedings regarding agency actions.<p>
<p>
*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Environmental</i> - Experience in representation of clients in the organic chemicals, synthetic
fibers, nonferrous metals, and semiconductor industries in regulation of hazardous waste,
toxic substance control, and air and water pollution control.  <p>
<p>
*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Utility</i> - Representation of industrial clients and utilities in the areas of electric utility
ratemaking, cogeneration, and telecommunications ratemaking, regulation, and competition.<p>
<p>
*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Technology</i> - Involvement with issues regarding new policies and regulatory frameworks as
applied to high technology related business and industry, in particular, the biotechnology 
and computer industries.<p>
<p>
</b><p>
<b> <i>Education</b></i><p>
<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;J.D., with Honors, <b> University of Texas School of Law</b>, 1982<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;M.A., Biochemistry, <b> University of Texas at Austin</b>, 1980<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;B.A., <i>Magna Cum Laude</i>, Chemistry, <b> Montclair State College</b>, 1977<p>
<p>
<p>
<i><b> Civic and Professional</i></b><p>
<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;American Bar Association (Science &amp; Technology; Natural Resources, Energy, and
Environmental Law ("SONREEL")  (National Committee Chairman, 1993-Present); and
Public Utility Law Sections)<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Eanes Independent School District, Church/State Relations Committee, 1993-present<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;State Bar of Texas <p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Travis County Bar Association<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Order of the Coif<p>
<p>
<p>
<i><b> Listings and Presentations</b></i><p>
<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"Hazardous Waste Identification Rule and the Metal Products &amp; Machinery Rule," SSA's
18th Annual International High Technology Safety, Industrial Hygiene &amp; Environmental
Conference, April 1996<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"Bioremediation: Boom or Bust?," Second Annual SONREEL Meeting, San Antonio,
1994<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"Administrative Penalties," State Bar of Texas Advanced Administrative Law Course,
1990 and 1993<p>
<b>*</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Editorial Board "Looking Ahead" (SONREEL) "Tech Talk"  Editor<p>
<p>
