<HEAD>
<TITLE>emery.htm </TITLE>
<BODY background="linen.gif" text="000000" link="2F4F2F" vlink="A62A2A">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="lprh_grn.gif">

<P><B>GENE EMERY</B>
</CENTER>
<P><B>SHAREHOLDER</B>
<BR><B>Federal Tax/Estate Planning and Probate</B>
<P><B><I>Practice Areas</I></B>

<P><li TYPE=SQUARE>Mr. Emery has extensive experience in sophisticated estate and tax
planning for clients whose estates consist of various types of assets including oil and gas
interests, real estate, stock and bond portfolios and closely held businesses.  He also has
extensive experience in gift and estate tax matters, trust and probate matters, and advice to
fiduciaries and in trust and fiduciary controversies and litigation, particularly in the Dallas
Probate Courts.
<P><li>He has severed as counsel to corporate trustees and trust departments on numerous
occasions.
<P><li>He has experience in handling matters for businesses of various types such as
manufacturing companies and independent oil producers including purchases and sales, mergers,
and drilling participation agreements.
<P><li>He has also rendered tax and business planning advice and obtained favorable tax rulings
in corporate mergers and other transactions.
<P><li>He has handled tax controversies at all levels, including administrative dealings with the
IRS, the U.S. Tax Court, the Claims Court, the U.S. Courts of Appeal, and U.S. District Courts. 
He has also worked with the Congressional Tax Writing Committees and the Treasury
Department in Washington, D.C. on tax legislation and regulations.

<P><B><I>Education</I></B>

<P><li>A.B., <U>magna</U> <U>cum</U> <U>laude</U>, University of Illinois, 1945
<P><li>LL.B., <U>cum</U> <U>laude</U>, Harvard Law School, 1948
<P><li>Phi Beta Kappa

<P><B><I>Civic and Professional</I></B>

<P><li>American Bar Association:  Gift and Estate Tax, Natural Resources and Corporate Tax
Committees of Tax Section
<P><li>Fellow, American College of Trust and Estate Counsel
<P><li>Fellow, American College of Tax Counsel
<P><li>Former President, Dallas Estate Council
<P><li>Former President, North Texas Chapter Arthritis Foundation
<P><li>Founding Board Member, Dallas Blue Foundation

<P><B><I>Listings and Presentations</I></B>

<P><li>Lecturer on several occasions on tax matters at Tulane Tax Institute, University of Texas
Tax Institute, Texas CPA Tax Institute, Texas CPA Estate Planning Institute, Southwestern
Legal Foundation Wills and Probate Institute, and many other institutes and programs
<P><li>Former Chairman of, and lecturer at, Oil and Gas and Taxation Institute of Southwestern
Legal Foundation
<P><li>Former faculty member, short course on Corporate Tax and Reorganizations, S.M.U.
<P><li>Listed, all editions, <U>Best Lawyers in America</U>


</BODY></HTML>
