<p>
<center><b> PETER A. FRANKLIN, III</b></center><p>
<p>
<b> SHAREHOLDER<p>
Bankruptcy - Section Administrator<p>
</b><p>
<b> </b><b> <i>Practice Areas</i></b><p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Substantial experience in:</i><p>
<p>
<b> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the area of creditors rights, bankruptcy&nbsp;and related litigation,<p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;representing parties with complex claims in Chapter 11 reorganizations, debtors and <p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;representing lenders, unsecured creditors, bankruptcy trustees, examiners, and creditors
committees.   <p>
</b><p>
<i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Franklin has represented parties in many of the major bankruptcy reorganizations which have occurred
throughout the United States in the last several years.</i><p>
<p>
<b> <i>Education</i></b><p>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;J.D., <b> Southern Methodist University School of Law</b>, 1969<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;B.A., <b> Ohio Wesleyan University</b>, 1966<p>
<i><b> </i></b><i><b> <p>
Civic and Professional</b><p>
</i><p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjunct Professor; Bankruptcy and Corporate Reorganization, Texas Tech University Law
School, 1983; <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjunct Professor; Advanced Bankruptcy, Southern Methodist University Law School, 1984-; <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Member and Past Chairman, 1986, Dallas and Texas Bar Associations Committee on
Relations with the Bankruptcy Judiciary; <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Co-Chairman, Southern Methodist University School of Law's Annual Advanced Bankruptcy
Seminar Series; <p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Member, American Bankruptcy Institute Subcommittee on Professional Fees and
Subcommittee on the FDIC and RTC; <p>
<p>
<i><b> Listings and Presentations</i></b><p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b> *</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;Chapter 7 Trustee V. Chapter 11 Professionals:  The Chapter 7 Trustee's Right To Recover
Previously Paid Chapter 11 Professional Fees,&quot; Norton Annual Survey of Bankruptcy Law,
1996; <p>
